org.arl.fjage

Class PoissonBehavior

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.arl.fjage.Behavior
      • org.arl.fjage.PoissonBehavior
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Behavior>

    public class PoissonBehavior
extends Behavior
    A behavior that simulates a Poisson arrival process. The onTick() method of this behavior is called with exponentially distributed random interarrival time.

      • PoissonBehavior

        public PoissonBehavior(long millis)
        Creates a behavior that simulates a Poisson arrival process with a specified average interarrival time. The equivalent arrival rate is given by the reciprocal of the average interarrival time.
        Parameters:
        millis - average interarrival time in milliseconds.
